The paper discusses the integration of interactive visualizations in digital libraries and information retrieval systems, which are primarily related to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of interactive graphics also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and data visualization (cs.DL). The paper also mentions the filtering and manipulation of search results, which is related to database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the use of interactive graphics to support the creation of new search queries and identify related metadata can be considered as a form of information extraction and retrieval (cs.SI).
